issue.title: Apex Amp causes model to fail tracing with a strange error

labels.name: triaged

repository.name: pytorch

issue.body:
I have a DenseNet-like model for speech recognition (https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.03288). My code:  https://github.com/vadimkantorov/convasr/blob/master/models.py#L94

When I export it to ONNX as is, everything works okay. When I apply `model = apex.amp.initialize(model, opt_level = 'O3')` prior to export (basically to have model params converted to float16 and have input/output casts from float32), I get this:

`RuntimeError: Cannot insert a Tensor that requires grad as a constant. Consider making it a parameter or input, or detaching the gradient`

The error is really strange.

issue.title: Handle nodes with dtype attribute causing diffs in inferred and actual types of NodeArgs due to InsertCastTransformer

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**:
 
Generator ONNX ops (RandomNormal, RandomNormalLike, EyeLike, etc.) have the type of the outputs inferred based on a static attribute (`dtype`) and this can cause mismatch between the actual type and the ONNX inferred type of a NodeArg after a pass through the `InsertCastTransformer`. Hence, we mutate the attribute of these nodes in the InsertCastTransformer so as to get a match between the ONNX inferred type and the actual type.

**Motivation and Context**
Fix https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/4405
